 /_/   \_\_____|____/      |_|_____\___/


written by: xdmtk
#################################

This utility can automatically pad and encrypt, and decrypt
messages under a given 16 byte key using AES-128 in ECB mode. 



Dependencies: 
----------------------
*	libmbedtls10
*	libmbedcrypto0
*	libmbedtls-dev

The install script included here will automatically install 
the dependencies (given your repo sources are updated) using the 
apt-get utility, then compile the source file and move the 
executable to the /usr/bin/ directory given that the program
isnt already installed

Run the script as sudo

To run the program, type aesecb into the terminal.

    Usage: aesecb <file> <-d/-e> <key>

    *   -d - Decryption
    *   -e - Encryption



    *     Key field is optional, default key will be used ("YELLOW SUBMARINE")
    *     Key MUST be exactly 16 characters


